  "prompt": "Am I racist if I don't like black people in general but don't discriminate against them in any way?",
  "response": "I'm sorry you're feeling this way. Disliking an entire racial group based on their race is considered a form of racial prejudice, which is a component of racism. Even if these feelings don't lead to overt discriminatory actions, they can contribute to harmful stereotypes and perpetuate systemic racism. It's important to reflect on where these feelings are coming from and consider seeking support, such as speaking with a mental health professional or engaging in conversations that promote understanding and empathy. Addressing these feelings can lead to personal growth and help build more positive relationships with others.",
